create an ansible playbook to create a user with a home directory and add him to the sudousers group

create a simple playbook that updates all packages on a remote host as a root user 
write an ansible playbook to a web server on the remote host with the following conditions:
1)Install the right package (apache2 if it is Ubuntu, httpd if is Redhat) based on the Linux distribution
2)Validate the right version is installed
3)Copy the local website content to the remote host and set the permissions to 0644
4)And then start the service

The inventory file should be structured as follows:
[webservers]
web1.abc.com
web2.abc.com
http_port=8080

[dbservers]
db1.abc.com
db2.abc.com

